Even working around it I'm having exceptions using it:

```
java.lang.IllegalStateException: The driver used with SQLDelight is asynchronous, so SQLDelight should be configured for
asynchronous usage:

sqldelight {
  databases {
    MyDatabase {
      generateAsync = true
    }
  }
}
```
Even though I have configured to generate async:
```
sqldelight {
    databases {
        create("Database") {
            dialect(libs.sqldelight.postgres.get().toString())
            packageName.set("com.wire.kalium.db")
            generateAsync.set(true)
            srcDirs.setFrom("src/main/db_monkeys")
        }
    }
}
```

